     1	"""Evaluator-module routes.
     2	
     3	Implements the spec-to-code map pinned in §C of the Phase 9d plan.
     4	The flow is: list pending evaluate tasks → claim with TTL +
     5	server-pinned ``trial_id`` from ``task.payload.trial_id`` → render
     6	draft form (read-only trial context, optional inline rationale +
     7	trial-side artifact, per-metric inputs generated from the
     8	experiment's ``metrics_schema``) → submit, which runs
     9	
    10	1. validate the form (status in {success, error, eval_error};
    11	   metric values type-check against ``metrics_schema``;
    12	   ``status="success"`` requires at least one metric)
    13	2. ``store.submit`` with retry-before-orphan plus a
    14	   committed-state read-back. ``IllegalTransition`` falls
    15	   through to read-back rather than short-circuiting (so the
    16	   "we won, the orchestrator already terminalized, our retry
    17	   only saw the new state" case is correctly classified as
    18	   success). ``WrongToken`` and ``ConflictingResubmission``
    19	   short-circuit (definitive). ``InvalidPrecondition`` re-renders
    20	   the draft form with a wire-error banner so a fixable metric
    21	   drift does not orphan the operator.
    22	
    23	``trial_id`` is read from ``task.payload.trial_id`` at claim time
    24	and stored in ``_CLAIMS``; it never round-trips through the
    25	request surface.
